          "name": "hotheadhacker",
          "url": "https://github.com/hotheadhacker/no-as-a-service"
        },
        "description": "No-as-a-Service (NaaS) is a simple API that returns a random rejection reason. Use it when you need a realistic excuse, a fun \"no,\" or want to simulate being turned down in style. Built for humans, excuses, and humor.",
        "license": {
          "name": "MIT",
          "url": "https://github.com/hotheadhacker/no-as-a-service/blob/main/LICENSE"
        },
        "servers": [
          {
            "description": "Production server",
            "url": "https://naas.isalman.dev"
          },
          {
            "description": "Local development server",
            "url": "http://localhost:3000"
          }
        ],
        "title": "No-as-a-Service API",
        "version": "1.0.0",
        "tagline": "Get a random, creatively-worded rejection reason on demand",
        "homepage": "https://naas.isalman.dev",
        "docs_url": "https://github.com/hotheadhacker/no-as-a-service",
        "license_short": "MIT License",
        "license_md": "- Licensed under the MIT License\n- Permits broad reuse, modification, and redistribution with minimal restrictions\n- Source available at [hotheadhacker/no-as-a-service](https://github.com/hotheadhacker/no-as-a-service)",
        "about_md": "No-as-a-Service is a small, free API that returns a random, often humorous rejection reason. It is maintained by [hotheadhacker](https://github.com/hotheadhacker) and hosted at `naas.isalman.dev`, with the source code available on GitHub under an MIT licence.\n\nWhat you get from the API:\n\n- A single `GET /no` endpoint\n- A JSON response with a `reason` field containing a randomly-selected excuse drawn from a pool of 1000+ rejection lines\n- Useful for demos, placeholder content, chat bots, screensavers, or anywhere you need a creative way to say no\n\nThe service has CORS enabled, requires no authentication, and applies a rate limit of 120 requests per minute per IP. The project is also packaged for self-hosting via Node.js, Docker, and devcontainers, so you can run your own instance if you prefer.",
        "entity_desc": {
          "rejection_reason": "A randomly-selected rejection excuse returned as a JSON `{ \"reason\": \"...\" }` payload from `GET /no`."
        },
